{"editorCode":";\tEnlarge a rectangle\n\n;Teacher asked 1st grade students to write a procedure that draws two rectangles. The 1st rectangle with dimensions 50,100 and the 2nd with dimensions  :a and :m \n\n;One rectangle should be within the other. The process should print the ratio of the dimensions of the two rectangles. \n \n;Kiki wrote the process \"rectangle\", defined it and executed as \"rectangle 150 200\". However the result was not the expected one. \n\n;Help Kiki to fix the procedure, so that it draws what the teacher asked.\n\n;Click the papyrus on the left to read detailed instructions.\n\n;----------PROCEDURES-------------\n\nTo rectangle :a :m\nrepeat 2[fd 50 rt 90 fd 100 rt 90]\nfd :a rt 90 \nfd :m rt 90\nfd :a lt 90\nfd :m rt 90\nprint 'Width - Ration (2nd/1st): '\nprint :a/50\nprint 'Length - Ratio (2nd/1st): '\nprint :m/100\nend\ncs\nrectangle 150 200\n\n\n\n\n","hiddenCode":[],"sceneCode":"","cameraPos":{"x":0,"y":1.2246467991473532e-14,"z":200},"character":"Bird","notes":"  Instructions \n-------------------------------------------------\nÎ±)  Define and run the procedure 'rectangle' to see what the bird draws on the scene. \n\nTo define the procedure, select the lines from the word \"TO\" to the word \"END\" and then press the \"Insert\" button on your keyboard or the \"Run Code\" (Play) button on the right top of the editor. \n\nTo run the procedure, click on the line \"rectangle 150 200\"and then press the \"Insert\" button on your keyboard or the \"Run Code\" (Play) button on the right top of the editor. \n\nb)  Fix the procedure, so that it draws what the teacher asked. \nRedefine the procedure, run it, and then change the values of the variables with the sliders to check if your modifications are correct. \nClick on the trace in the scene to enable the sliders too.\n\nc) Run the procedure with the right values to have \nI)a length ratio of 2.\nII) both ratios of 2,5. \nRatios are printed in the yellow window below the editor","sliders":{}